Basic Setup
-----------
# Connect to device
adb devices
adb connect <device_ip>:<port>

# Check device info
adb shell getprop ro.product.model


ðŸ”§ Device management
-----------------
# List connected devices
adb devices -l

# Connect over WiFi
adb tcpip 5555
adb connect <device_ip>

# Reboot devices
adb reboot
adb reboot bootloader
adb reboot recovery


ðŸ“± App Management
-----------------
# Install/Uninstall apps
adb install app.apk
adb install -r app.apk  # Reinstall
adb uninstall com.package.name

# List packages
adb shell pm list packages
adb shell pm list packages -3  # Third-party apps


ðŸ“Š Log Collection & Analysis
----------------------------
# Basic logcat
adb logcat
adb logcat -d > logs.txt

# Filter by tag/priority
adb logcat -s TAG_NAME
adb logcat *:E  # Errors only

# Clear logs
adb logcat -c

# Logcat with timestamps
adb logcat -v time


ðŸ› Debugging & Testing
----------------------
# Take screenshot
adb exec-out screencap -p > screenshot.png

# Screen recording (Android 4.4+)
adb shell screenrecord /sdcard/demo.mp4
adb pull /sdcard/demo.mp4

# Monitor CPU/Memory
adb shell top
adb shell dumpsys meminfo <package_name>


âš¡ Performance Testing
----------------------
# Battery info
adb shell dumpsys battery

# Network stats
adb shell dumpsys netstats

# GPU profiling
adb shell dumpsys gfxinfo <package_name>


ðŸ› ï¸ QA-Specific Scripts
----------------------
Check the scripts/ directory for ready-to-use scripts:

log-capture.sh - Automated log collection

screen-record.sh - Screen recording with timestamp

install-multiple.sh - Batch APK installation

bug-report.sh - Comprehensive bug report generation


ðŸ“– Best Practices for QA
------------------------
1. Consistent Log Collection
# Always include:
adb logcat -d -v time > logs_$(date +%Y%m%d_%H%M%S).txt
adb bugreport > bugreport_$(date +%Y%m%d).zip

2. Device State Verification
# Before testing
adb shell getprop
adb shell dumpsys battery
adb shell wm size

3. Automation Support
# Grant permissions for automated testing
adb shell pm grant <package> android.permission.<PERMISSION>


ðŸŽ¯ Real-World QA Scenarios
--------------------------
Scenario 1: Crash Investigation
# 1. Reproduce the crash
# 2. Capture logs immediately
adb logcat -d --pid=$(adb shell pidof -s com.package.name) > crash.log
# 3. Get stack trace
adb logcat -d | grep -A 20 -B 5 "FATAL"

Scenario 2: Performance Testing
# Monitor during test execution
adb shell top -n 1 -d 1 > cpu_usage.txt &
adb shell dumpsys gfxinfo com.package.name reset
# Execute test...
adb shell dumpsys gfxinfo com.package.name > gfxinfo.txt

Scenario 3: Installation Testing
# Test clean install
adb uninstall com.package.name
adb install app.apk

# Test upgrade
adb install -r upgrade.apk
adb shell am start -n com.package.name/.MainActivity


